<h1> A Blazor GUI served by ServiceStack Middleware hosted in a .Net Core 2.1 IntegratedIISInProcess WebHost.</h1>
<P>The server in this demo uses a TargetFramework: Net Core 2.1 and a WebHost: IntegratedIISInProcess</P>

<h2>Demo's point</h2>
<p>To demonstrate Blazor logging, and a simple page-local variable, and a synchronous event handler to increment that variable</p>
<h3>GUI changes</h3>
<p>The GUI implements logging to the browser's Console using `Microsoft.Extensions.Logging` and a third-party logging package `Blazor.Extensions.Logging`</p>
<p>The GUI implements a integer page-local Property, and a button, which increments the value of the Property.</p>
<h3>Server changes</h3>
<p>The Server project appears, Targets .Net Core 2.1 and provides an IntegratedIISInProcess WebHost</p>
<p></p>
<h2>Developer tools</h2>
<p>Having the browser's Developer Tools window open, showing the Console window, will display the logging message from the GUI in the Console window. The links below in Attribution [ToDo: Link it] contain further reading on the browser's Developer Tools and Console Window.</p>
<h2>Visual portion</h2>
<p>The number below is stored in a page-local Property named AnIntegerProperty. The number will increment with each button click, but will reset to 0 if the page is initialized. Initialing loading the page initializes it. Refreshing the page (browser refresh button) is another way to initialze the page.</p>
<p>AnIntegerProperty: @AnIntegerProperty</p>
<button name="IncrementAInteger" class="btn btn-primary" @onclick="@IncrementAnIntegerPropertyButtonOnClick">click to increment</button>
<p>This page does not use any storage so `AnIntegerProperty` re-initializes to its default value (0) each time the page is initialized</p>
